    "eROSITA spectra of the SNR 1E 0102-7219, taken with TM12346 in Nov 2019 and 2021.",
    "An exemplary detector light curve of TM 6 for a bright source passing through the field of view and the resulting Bayesian Blocks is shown in Fig.",
    "Example detector light curve (blue) of TM 6 of one telemetry file with bins 5 s in length.The segmentation created by the Bayesian Blocks algorithm is shown in red and the identified intervals of bright sources in the field of view are shaded green.",
    "Note that the very short block at t ≈ 1400 s was caused by a remaining corrupt frame.",
    "The block of elevated count rate towards the end of the light curve was caused by an unknown transient X-ray source detected on New Year's Eve 2019(Wilms et al. 2020)."
